    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Move-only handle to a server-side <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_voice_input" kindref="compound">VoiceInput</ref> session.</para>
<para>Obtained via <ref refid="class_tryll_1_1_client_1_1_tryll_client_1af7a7f76f8a1105229c566745495b19d2" kindref="member">TryllClient::CreateVoiceInput</ref> or CreateVoiceInputAsync.</para>
<para>Lifetime guarantee: the destructor issues an implicit CancelUtterance (if active) followed by DestroyVoiceInput so the server-side ISttSession is always cleaned up. Move the handle to extend its lifetime.</para>
<para>Thread-safety: this handle is NOT internally synchronized. All public methods — including SendAudioBuffer — must be called from the same thread, or the caller must provide external synchronization. Moving or destroying the handle must likewise be serialized with any concurrent method calls. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
